<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="443" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Burlingame</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 78.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-20"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 20, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 1st of June last, No.
                            76, placing before me your action in relation to the case of David
                            Williams, tried, convicted, and sentenced for murder, has been received.
                            In reply, I have to express my approval of your proceedings.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Anson Burlingame</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>